hat explore the status, experiences and future prospects of the dynamic library and information science practice.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aInformation services. 0aLibraries. 4aInformationschaos. 4aInformationsdienste. 4aInformationszeitalter. 4aInternationale Zusammenarbeit. 4aNachhaltige Gesellschaft.  aInformation services.  ainformation age.  ainformation disorder.  ainternational cooperation.1 aAlabi, Raliat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlbright, Kendra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAsimah, Amy P. A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAyodeji Ajani, Yusuf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAzeroual, Otmane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBangani, Siviwe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoloka, Mamotshabo Johanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBosire Onyancha, Omwoyo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChidimma Ojobor, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChikonzo, Agnes C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChisita, Collence Takaingenhamo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDamilola Omoike, Adenike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEmanuel Matlala, Mpubane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarrugia, Charles J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFolorunso Ayanbode, Oluyemi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFombad, Madeleine C., econtributor.